FROM node:20-alpine

WORKDIR /app

COPY package*.json ./
RUN npm install

COPY . .
# source      = . → your local machine current folder
#                   everything in it
# destination = . → current WORKDIR inside container
#                   which is /app

# Same as: COPY . /app         # explicit version ✅

EXPOSE 3000

CMD ["npm", "start"]


----------
Pipeline for this:

pipeline {
    agent any
    stages {
        stage('Checkout') {
            steps {
                git 'https://github.com/example/app.git'
            }
        }
        stage('Docker Build') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker build -t myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER} .'
            }
        }
        stage('Push Image') {
            steps {
                sh 'docker push myapp:${BUILD_NUMBER}'
            }
        }
        stage('Deploy to K8s') {
            steps {
                sh 'kubectl apply -f deployment.yaml'
            }
        }
    }
}
----------------------------------------
No Build stage — because npm install happens inside Docker via RUN npm install, not in the pipeline.

Java vs Node comparison:

+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
|             | Java (Maven)                         | Node.js                   |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Build step  | mvn clean package in pipeline        | npm install inside        |
|             |                                      | Dockerfile                |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Output      | target/app.jar                       | node_modules + source     |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Base image  | eclipse-temurin:21-jre              | node:20-alpine            |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Port        | 8080                                 | 3000                      |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+
| Start cmd   | java -jar app.jar                    | npm start                 |
+-------------+--------------------------------------+---------------------------+

Why COPY package*.json ./ first?

Docker layer caching:
- If only source code changes, Docker skips npm install
  and reuses the cached layer.
- This results in faster builds.
